author: CNN
description: White House envoy Steve Witkoff meets Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu today in New York, ahead of Netanyahu’s White House meeting with President Trump tomorrow. Trump says a Gaza peace deal is near, centered on a 21-point plan with a ceasefire, hostage release, and postwar governance. CNN analyst and New York Times correspondent David Sanger joins CNN to discuss.   #CNN #News
title: Witkoff to meet Netanyahu before high-stakes White House talks

author: CNN
description: In a post that has since been deleted, President Donald Trump shared an apparent AI video of himself promoting a cure-all bed with origins in conspiratorial corners of the internet. CNN's Jake Tapper reports.
title: Trump shares apparent AI video promoting ‘medbed’ conspiracy theory

author: CNN
description: At least two people were killed and eight others were wounded in a shooting at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Grand Blanc Township, Michigan, police said. #CNN #News
title: Deadly shooting and fire at church in Michigan

author: CNN
description: At least two people were killed and eight others wounded today in a shooting at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Grand Blanc Township, Michigan, police said.   #CNN #News
title: Officials respond to deadly shooting and fire at church in Michigan

author: CNN
description: New York Mayor Eric Adams announced today he is ending his reelection campaign. CNN's Gloria Pazmino shares what we know about the decision, and what it could mean for the race.               #CNN #News
title: Eric Adams withdraws from New York City mayoral race

author: CNN
description: A 40-year-old man is facing murder charges after allegedly pulling up on a boat to a waterfront bar in North Carolina Saturday night and opening fire, killing three and injuring at least eight others.
title: Shooting at North Carolina waterfront bar leaves 3 dead

author: CNN
description: Fareed Zakaria argues that the Trump administration seems to be ignoring and flouting laws and rules purposefully, so as to erode the checks on its authority. #CNN #News
title: Fareed's Take: The White House is playing fast and loose with all sorts of rules

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Fareed Zakaria sits down with Poland’s deputy Prime Minister Radosław Sikorski, who warns that Russia’s recent drone and jet incursions into NATO airspace are deliberate provocations and part of Moscow’s hybrid war.  #CNN #News
title: Polish official issues warning about Russia's incursions into NATO airspace

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper speaks with former deputy FBI director Andrew McCabe about James Comey's indictment. #CNN #News
title: Andrew McCabe: Trump targeting Comey should 'terrify every person in this country'

author: CNN
description: Multiple people have been injured in a shooting at the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Grand Blanc, Michigan, according to police. The shooter is down but a fire has broken out at the church, according to local authorities, who urged residents to stay out of the area. #CNN #News
title: At least one dead and nine injured in Michigan church shooting

author: CNN
description: House Speaker Mike Johnson joins CNN's Jake Tapper to discuss the looming government shutdown and President Trump's pressure campaign on the Justice Department to go after his political opponents. #CNN #News
title: Speaker Johnson hits Dems' 'absurd' shutdown demands, defends Comey indictment

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump told reporters he expects other political opponents to be prosecuted after the indictment of former FBI Director James Comey. The administration’s efforts to go after Trump’s political opponents come as they’re also ramping up investigations of unnamed groups they’ve accused of supporting political violence.

In the Oval Office on Thursday, Trump said he thought Democratic billionaire donor George Soros — one of the right’s favorite targets — was a “likely candidate” for investigation.

CNN's Manu Raju discusses with his "Inside Politics" panel. #CNN #News
title: Trump's campaign of retribution accelerates

author: CNN
description:
Immigration officers have detained Ian Roberts, the superintendent of Des Moines Public Schools — Iowa’s largest school district. The Department of Homeland Security says Roberts was in the country illegally and has weapon possession charges.

#CNN #News #ICE #Iowa #IanRoberts
title: ICE arrests popular Iowa school superintendent

author: CNN
description: CNN's Manu Raju discusses the possibility of a government shutdown and the Monday meeting between President Trump and Congressional leadership with his "Inside Politics" panel: CNN White House reporter Alayna Treene, the Dispatch's Jonah Goldberg, the Atlanta Journal's Tia Mitchell, and Semafor's Burgess Everett. #CNN #News
title: New Trump meeting: Will Democrats' shutdown gamble pay off?

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump has sent the military to Portland, Oregon. CNN military analyst retired Col. Cedric Leighton explains what to expect next, and discusses Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth’s surprise gathering of hundreds of generals and admirals in Virginia. #CNN #News
title: CNN military analyst reacts to Trump's plan to send troops to Portland

author: CNN
description: Veronica Miracle speaks with CNN chief media analyst Brian Stelter about the new season of CBS's "60 Minutes", the new restrictions on the press imposed by Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth, and his analysis of how pushback from viewers, advertisers and employees ultimately brought Jimmy Kimmel's show back to the airwaves. #CNN #News
title: '60 Minutes' returns after tumultuous season

author: CNN
description:
A Kyiv resident tells CNN what it was like to be fired on by one of the more than 600 drones and missiles Russia launched across Ukraine in one of the largest barrages of the war.

#CNN #News #Ukraine
title: Man describes Kyiv attack that destroyed his home

author: CNN
description: Dozens were killed and over 50 injured in a crowd crush while at a rally held by Tamil actor-turned politician, Vijay. #cnn #news #india #crowdcrush
title: Relatives grieve victims of deadly crowd crush

author: CNN
description: A crowd crush at a political rally in India resulted in dozens of deaths and injuries. An investigation into the incident is underway. CNN's Will Ripley reports on the tragedy and the questions that have followed over safety measures. #cnn #news #india
title: India crowd crush turns deadly at political rally

author: CNN
description: China opened the world’s tallest bridge on Sunday in Guizhou province. Measuring 2,051 feet above river level, this steel truss suspension bridge breaks the record previously held by the Millau Viaduct in France. Construction began in January 2022. #cnn #news #china #guizhou
title: World's tallest bridge opens in China

author: CNN
description: Jia Lynn Yang of The New York Times joins CNN's Michael Smerconish to discuss whether US political violence is driven less by ideology and more by despair among socially isolated young men. Recent attacks, from the Charlie Kirk assassination to the Butler attempt on President Trump, often involve individuals with little political engagement, making prevention difficult. Experts stress focusing on mental health and isolation rather than partisan labels.   #CNN #News
title: Analysis: Are young men’s political attacks fueled more by beliefs or by personal struggles?

author: CNN
description: Roy Wood Jr. discusses this week's news with his panel, including Donald Trump’s run-in with an escalator and more. “Have I Got News For You” regularly airs Saturdays at 9pm ET/PT and streams on HBO Max the following day.   #CNN #News
title: Comedians react to Trump’s latest ‘adversary’: An escalator

author: CNN
description: During the second day of the Ryder Cup, Team USA tried to close the gap. After a series of matches, the score now stands at 11.5 to 4.5 - a “disaster” that would take a miracle to overcome, CNN’s Don Riddell reports.
title: Analysis: Ryder Cup has been a 'disaster' for Team USA

author: CNN
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu will visit the White House Monday following a defiant UN speech, with the Trump administration’s 21-point Gaza peace plan on the agenda. CNN’s Jessica Dean discusses the development with CNN political and global affairs analyst Barak Ravid.   #CNN #News
title: Netanyahu set for White House talks Monday after defiant UN remarks

author: CNN
description: President Trump told reporters he expects additional political opponents to face prosecution following the indictment of former FBI Director James Comey. The Justice Department charged Comey on Thursday, just days after Trump pushed for his prosecution and removed the prosecutor who resisted targeting the president’s rivals. CNN’s Jessica Dean discusses the development with senior legal analyst Elie Honig.   #CNN #News
title: Trump eyes other political adversaries in wake of Comey charges
